messages.content: lets finish our index file website

I've noticed that the `index.html` file is missing a crucial section that highlights the brands you specialize in. To enhance the user experience and provide more value to your customers, I'll add a "Shop by Brand" section.

This new section will feature the logos of the brands you work with, making it easy for users to navigate to the products they're interested in. The brands I'll include are Stiletto, Ryobi, Husky, Inkabi, and Insika. I'll also add a new CSS class to the stylesheet for the brand logos.

I'll start by adding the "Shop by Brand" section to the `index.html` file.

thoughts.subject: Reviewing the HTML File
thoughts.description: I've initiated a review of the `index.html` file, beginning with a thorough read-through. My goal is to grasp the existing structure and content before making any modifications. The aim is to ensure any new additions are seamlessly integrated and maintain the page's overall integrity.

thoughts.subject: Reviewing the Structure
thoughts.description:
\n\n

I've taken a look at the provided HTML structure. I'm focusing on the existing sections like "Our Services" and "About Us". My current task is to consider what additional content or refinements would best serve the overall user experience. I am currently evaluating potential improvements to these sections.

thoughts.subject: Assessing Content Strategy
thoughts.description:
\n\n

I've now pinpointed several potential areas for expansion within the existing framework.  I'm leaning towards enriching the "Our Services" section with more detailed descriptions. Furthermore, I'm contemplating visual enhancements, such as integrating a photo gallery for a more engaging user experience. The next stage involves refining the layout to optimize the flow.
